WEBVTT

00:02.585 --> 00:04.737
Ruby:
Hey, now.

00:04.805 --> 00:07.573
♪♪

00:07.641 --> 00:09.875
it's got to be 100 degrees
in the shade today.

00:09.944 --> 00:12.911
I-I was hoping I could
trouble you for a sip.

00:12.980 --> 00:14.029
You work around here?

00:14.065 --> 00:16.198
Just down the road
at the shurden place.

00:16.217 --> 00:18.650
I-I cut through here sometimes
on my way to the market.

00:18.719 --> 00:20.452
Saves me a few steps.

00:22.923 --> 00:24.490
You could fry an egg
in this heat today.

00:24.558 --> 00:26.525
Sure could.

00:26.627 --> 00:28.077
Thank you.

00:28.162 --> 00:29.244
Thank you.

00:29.330 --> 00:31.964
♪♪

00:32.033 --> 00:33.549
[ water rushing ]

00:33.584 --> 00:35.467
down at the shurden place,
all anybody can talk about

00:35.586 --> 00:38.904
these days is that
till boy turned up dead.

00:38.989 --> 00:40.839
Some folks say he was
seen around here

00:40.925 --> 00:42.224
the morning
he went missing.

00:42.309 --> 00:43.375
[ grunts ]

00:43.444 --> 00:45.527
you hear anything
like that?

00:45.613 --> 00:48.347
Folks say
a lot of things.

00:48.432 --> 00:50.416
But I ain't got time
for gossip.

00:50.484 --> 00:52.668
[ panting ]
you take care now.

00:52.753 --> 00:55.637
♪♪

00:55.689 --> 00:57.906
I don't work at the
shurden place, ma'am.

00:57.992 --> 00:59.608
My name
is ruby hurley.

00:59.693 --> 01:00.976
I work for the
national association

01:01.011 --> 01:02.061
for the advancement
of colored people,

01:02.179 --> 01:03.445
and I've been chasing
down leads all day

01:03.497 --> 01:04.980
to try to find the folks
that saw emmett till

01:05.082 --> 01:06.581
on the morning
that he was murdered.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.834
From what I hear, you might
be one of those folks.

01:08.903 --> 01:11.320
I ain't seen nothin',
and I ain't got nothin' to say.

01:11.405 --> 01:13.955
Ma'am, that boy was hunted down
and killed in cold blood.

01:14.058 --> 01:16.191
Now, if you know something,
you can expose the truth.

01:16.243 --> 01:17.859
And what good
is that gon' do?

01:17.912 --> 01:19.728
He's dead!
Look!

01:21.148 --> 01:22.448
I know that
you're scared.

01:22.566 --> 01:24.600
I-I know that you'd be
risking y-your job

01:24.635 --> 01:25.851
and your livelihood
to come forward.

01:25.936 --> 01:27.953
"livelihood"?

01:28.038 --> 01:29.888
I been picking cotton
all my life,

01:29.974 --> 01:31.607
and I'm still waitin'
to make a profit.

01:31.659 --> 01:34.093
That is exactly what
I am talking about.

01:34.178 --> 01:35.461
Nothing is gonna
change for us

01:35.529 --> 01:36.945
unless folks like you
come forward.

01:36.997 --> 01:40.783
And if you don't, who's to say
it won't be your child next?

01:40.868 --> 01:49.341
♪♪

01:49.410 --> 01:51.543
all I saw was a truck
parked over

01:51.629 --> 01:53.946
at the shed
that morning...

01:54.014 --> 01:56.115
And -- and four white men
standing around.

01:56.200 --> 01:58.600
Did you recognize
any of those men?

01:58.636 --> 02:00.235
I didn't get
a good look.

02:00.321 --> 02:02.187
♪♪

02:02.256 --> 02:05.023
but one of them
was tall and...

02:05.109 --> 02:06.458
Was kind of
bald-headed.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.177
I heard emmett till
was seen in the back

02:08.262 --> 02:10.112
of a truck
with two negro men.

02:10.147 --> 02:12.280
Did you see
any of them?

02:12.383 --> 02:14.049
No.

02:14.101 --> 02:16.485
But I know someone over
at the shurden place.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.021
Name's willie reed.

02:19.073 --> 02:22.808
He saw that boy.
And those other men, too.

02:22.877 --> 02:25.043
Only he says there was
three of them in the back.

02:25.112 --> 02:27.579
Three men
were with emmett?

02:27.648 --> 02:30.115
♪♪

02:30.184 --> 02:31.383
where can I find
willie reed?

02:31.468 --> 02:33.051
I don't know.

02:33.154 --> 02:34.653
He went missing
a couple of days ago,

02:34.722 --> 02:36.588
and ain't nobody
seen him since.

02:36.674 --> 02:39.124
♪♪

02:39.193 --> 02:42.077
-- captions by vitac --

02:43.531 --> 02:46.064
news announcer:<i> Jury selection</i>
<i> began yesterday in the trial</i>

02:46.133 --> 02:48.534
<i> against j.W. Milam</i>
<i> and roy bryant --</i>

02:48.619 --> 02:51.937
<i> the two men accused of killing</i>
<i> 14-year-old negro emmett till.</i>

02:52.022 --> 02:54.039
<i> Noticeably missing</i>
<i> was mamie bradley,</i>

02:54.124 --> 02:56.041
<i> mother of the alleged victim,</i>

02:56.143 --> 02:58.426
<i> but the courtroom was packed</i>
<i> with spectators.</i>

02:58.529 --> 03:00.528
<i> Many mississippi locals</i>
<i> complained about</i>

03:00.581 --> 03:02.731
<i> the level of publicity</i>
<i> this case has drawn</i>

03:02.766 --> 03:05.334
<i> and what some believe has been</i>
<i> an unfair portrayal</i>

03:05.419 --> 03:06.685
<i> of their region.</i>

03:06.754 --> 03:08.169
<i> This trial comes at a time</i>

03:08.222 --> 03:10.873
<i> when racial tensions continue</i>
<i> to escalate in the area,</i>

03:10.908 --> 03:14.159
<i>as several negro activists were</i>
<i> shot dead in recent months</i>

03:14.261 --> 03:16.078
<i> with no arrests made.</i>

03:16.113 --> 03:18.380
<i> The discovery of the body</i>
<i> alleged to be till</i>

03:18.432 --> 03:20.649
<i> has set off a series</i>
<i> of protest rallies</i>

03:20.734 --> 03:22.417
<i> led by the naacp.</i>

03:22.453 --> 03:24.436
<i> At one event held in chicago,</i>

03:24.521 --> 03:26.905
<i> mamie bradley reportedly</i>
<i> referred to mississippi</i>

03:26.991 --> 03:29.758
<i> as a "den of snakes."</i>

03:29.810 --> 03:31.743
yeah, we were out there
half the night.

03:31.812 --> 03:33.278
I was just about ready
to give up,

03:33.347 --> 03:35.514
but the chief here
managed to track down

03:35.583 --> 03:37.816
willie reed's grandfather
and get him to talk.

03:37.902 --> 03:40.035
Turns out he was on the
plantation that morning, too.

03:40.120 --> 03:41.820
Said he heard
sounds of beating

03:41.922 --> 03:43.889
coming from the shed,

03:43.958 --> 03:46.441
and someone screamin'.

03:46.477 --> 03:48.460
But did he actually
lay eyes on emmett?

03:48.529 --> 03:50.762
No. Apparently, the only one
who did was willie reed,

03:50.831 --> 03:52.331
and I got the sense
from the grandfather

03:52.433 --> 03:54.533
that willie's hiding out
'cause he's too scared to talk.

03:54.568 --> 03:58.036
So, bryant and milam had at
least two white accomplices,

03:58.122 --> 04:00.239
one who fits the description
of milam's brother.

04:00.307 --> 04:02.157
Mm-hmm.
And I'd wager that two
of the negro men

04:02.209 --> 04:03.659
who were in the back
of the truck

04:03.711 --> 04:04.977
are the same fellas
I heard about

04:05.062 --> 04:06.778
at the dance hall --
"too tight"

04:06.864 --> 04:07.913
and henry lee loggins.

04:07.982 --> 04:09.248
Yeah, one of them
has to be the third man

04:09.316 --> 04:11.250
who went with bryant
and milam to mose wright's.

04:11.352 --> 04:12.400
So, where are they?

04:12.453 --> 04:13.719
Well, either they're
hiding out like willie reed

04:13.837 --> 04:15.303
or someone's
keeping them quiet.

04:15.356 --> 04:17.289
We don't have enough
evidence to place emmett

04:17.374 --> 04:19.441
at that plantation
without any of them.

04:19.476 --> 04:21.393
But we do have enough
to take this public,

04:21.462 --> 04:23.729
call for further
investigation.

04:23.814 --> 04:25.614
This is our last chance
to get this case

04:25.666 --> 04:27.132
moved out of
tallahatchie county

04:27.201 --> 04:28.884
and out of sheriff strider's
jurisdiction.

04:28.936 --> 04:30.319
Then let's run the story.
Dr. Howard: No.

04:30.371 --> 04:31.586
If we go to press now,

04:31.622 --> 04:33.472
we put those witnesses'
lives in jeopardy.

04:33.540 --> 04:35.407
No, we have to get them
to safety first.

04:35.509 --> 04:37.759
And how can we protect them
if we can't even find them?

04:37.794 --> 04:40.162
If jury selection wraps up
this morning as scheduled,

04:40.197 --> 04:41.647
they'll begin
hearing testimony,

04:41.682 --> 04:43.849
and we won't be able to
introduce any new evidence.

04:43.917 --> 04:45.751
Which is why we need
the authorities.

04:45.853 --> 04:48.820
They have the resources
to find those witnesses

04:48.889 --> 04:50.071
and finish what we started.

04:50.124 --> 04:51.356
Or make it all
disappear.

04:51.458 --> 04:52.658
Exactly.

04:52.743 --> 04:54.626
Sheriff strider
wants this case,

04:54.662 --> 04:57.029
and he won't let it leave
this county without a fight.

04:57.114 --> 04:59.965
He's dirty
and connected.

05:00.084 --> 05:02.117
We have to be careful
who we involve.

05:02.202 --> 05:04.303
What about chatham?

05:04.338 --> 05:06.438
By all appearances,
he's putting in the work --

05:06.507 --> 05:08.073
a good-faith effort.

05:09.243 --> 05:10.409
Think we can trust him?

05:10.511 --> 05:11.576
Maybe.

05:11.679 --> 05:13.278
And his associate,
robert smith --

05:13.380 --> 05:15.247
uh, he's former fbi.

05:15.332 --> 05:17.215
[ clicks tongue ] it doesn't
matter who we go to.

05:17.284 --> 05:19.117
They're not gon'
listen to us.

05:19.219 --> 05:21.286
On a good day, they see us
as outside agitators

05:21.405 --> 05:23.171
with no business
in local affairs.

05:23.223 --> 05:24.456
On every other day,
we're just a bunch

05:24.525 --> 05:26.675
of uppity negroes
causing trouble.

05:27.845 --> 05:30.462
You got a better idea?

05:30.547 --> 05:33.098
What if chatham learns
about the witnesses

05:33.167 --> 05:35.751
from someone else?

05:35.803 --> 05:37.969
Someone who can
hold him accountable.

05:39.423 --> 05:40.972
Someone white.

05:41.008 --> 05:44.843
Yeah, and he would have no
choice but to take it seriously.

05:44.928 --> 05:47.346
Question is...

05:47.414 --> 05:49.481
Who can we trust
with something this big?

05:49.583 --> 05:51.817
♪♪

05:51.885 --> 05:53.869
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:57.725 --> 05:58.807
man: Hey, there she is.

05:58.892 --> 06:00.058
-Hey!
-Hey!

06:00.160 --> 06:02.310
-Mrs. Bradley?
-Mamie!

06:02.413 --> 06:03.862
-Mrs. Bradley?
-Mamie, over here!

06:03.947 --> 06:05.364
Man: Mamie,
what evidence do you have

06:05.449 --> 06:06.865
that's relevant
to the case?

06:06.950 --> 06:08.149
Are you here
to seek revenge?

06:08.252 --> 06:09.868
-Mrs. Bradley?
-Over here.

06:09.953 --> 06:12.587
What do you intend
to do here today?

06:12.673 --> 06:15.173
[ reporters shouting ]

06:15.292 --> 06:18.310
I am here to answer
any questions that my --

06:18.429 --> 06:21.313
that the a-attorneys may ask me
to answer to the best --

06:21.398 --> 06:24.866
do you have any evidence
bearing on this case?

06:24.918 --> 06:27.152
I-I do know that
this is my son.

06:27.237 --> 06:29.221
How do you respond
to local citizens

06:29.306 --> 06:31.039
who say
a civilized mother

06:31.091 --> 06:33.909
would never have put a child's
body on public display?

06:33.961 --> 06:36.812
We've looked away
for too long.

06:36.847 --> 06:40.182
Opening my son's casket
made it impossible to ignore

06:40.217 --> 06:42.601
what really
goes on down here.

06:42.686 --> 06:44.503
What about your son's
father, ma'am?

06:44.571 --> 06:45.937
Where is he?
[ cap guns firing ]

06:46.006 --> 06:47.656
[ laughter ]

06:47.708 --> 06:52.611
♪♪

06:52.679 --> 06:53.879
just keep moving.

06:53.997 --> 06:58.150
♪♪

06:58.268 --> 06:59.167
deputy:
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:59.203 --> 07:01.052
I'm gonna need
you boys to stop.

07:01.138 --> 07:02.687
Hold your hands out
to the side.

07:02.806 --> 07:04.256
♪♪

07:04.324 --> 07:05.240
it's okay.

07:05.292 --> 07:07.876
Just wait for us
over there.

07:07.978 --> 07:08.977
Come on.

07:09.062 --> 07:12.380
♪♪

07:12.416 --> 07:14.549
[ sighs ] alright.

07:14.635 --> 07:15.667
Come on.

07:15.769 --> 07:19.221
♪♪

07:19.256 --> 07:21.973
I'm fine. Just wrinkled
my good shirt, that's all.

07:22.042 --> 07:24.609
Deputy: [ sighs ]
alright, go ahead.

07:24.695 --> 07:30.415
♪♪

07:30.484 --> 07:32.050
[ indistinct conversations ]

07:32.119 --> 07:34.820
♪♪

07:34.905 --> 07:36.621
[ flashbulbs snapping ]

07:44.631 --> 07:46.314
[ sighs ] mr. Booker.

07:46.366 --> 07:48.133
What a relief to see
a familiar face.

07:48.252 --> 07:49.134
Mm.

07:49.219 --> 07:50.986
My goodness,
it's hot in here.

07:51.021 --> 07:52.671
It's supposed to be
95 degrees today,

07:52.739 --> 07:54.005
and that's
just outside.

07:54.074 --> 07:56.675
Get your
ice-cold sodas.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.526
Don't worry, we got
plenty of water with us

07:58.579 --> 07:59.928
at the press table.

08:01.014 --> 08:03.114
Meet ruby hurley
from the naacp.

08:03.217 --> 08:06.401
[ sighs ]
mrs. Bradley.

08:06.487 --> 08:07.903
Oh. [ laughs ]

08:07.988 --> 08:09.754
you made it.

08:09.840 --> 08:11.890
It is such an honor.
Thank you.

08:11.975 --> 08:13.942
I-I must admit,
you're the first woman

08:13.994 --> 08:15.560
I've met in the naacp.

08:15.679 --> 08:17.028
We are few, but fierce.

08:17.097 --> 08:18.479
Well, I'd say so.

08:18.532 --> 08:20.265
So, what is it
that you do?

08:20.350 --> 08:22.317
Oh, I'm the
southeastern director,

08:22.369 --> 08:24.052
which basically means
I travel around

08:24.087 --> 08:25.387
to the worst sections
of the country

08:25.439 --> 08:27.155
raising hell
in the name of justice.

08:27.207 --> 08:30.225
[ chuckles ]
ruby leads an army
of 35,000

08:30.260 --> 08:32.861
and is probably the only one
to receive death threats

08:32.913 --> 08:34.429
and marriage proposals
in equal measure.

08:34.515 --> 08:36.431
It's a hazard of the job.

08:36.483 --> 08:37.899
Sometimes you gotta
flip your hips

08:37.985 --> 08:39.417
if you want to get people
to talk to you.

08:39.503 --> 08:40.986
[ chuckles ] well,
it's good to know

08:41.054 --> 08:42.637
that women are a part
of the movement.

08:42.689 --> 08:45.340
Oh, we're not
just part of it.

08:45.392 --> 08:46.775
We're essential to it.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.478
And seeing you fighting
for your child

08:50.514 --> 08:53.081
is gonna inspire other women
to do the same.

08:58.488 --> 09:00.005
Strider:
Mamie bradley.

09:00.073 --> 09:02.774
Nice of you to join us.

09:02.843 --> 09:03.992
Your subpoena.

09:04.077 --> 09:06.394
♪♪

09:06.430 --> 09:09.397
you are now officially
a witness in this trial.

09:09.449 --> 09:11.216
While you are here,
you will come under

09:11.318 --> 09:12.817
all rules of mississippi.

09:12.886 --> 09:15.036
Understood?
Yes, sir.

09:15.138 --> 09:23.094
♪♪

09:23.163 --> 09:31.169
♪♪

09:31.288 --> 09:39.244
♪♪

09:39.346 --> 09:41.963
my god, they allow children
in the courtroom?

09:42.049 --> 09:43.815
♪♪

09:43.900 --> 09:45.200
all rise.

09:45.285 --> 09:48.653
♪♪

09:53.010 --> 09:55.126
[ flashbulb snaps ]
the court is now
in session.

09:55.195 --> 09:57.128
The honorable
judge swango presiding.

09:57.197 --> 09:58.546
Please be seated.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.167
Swango: Thank you.

10:02.252 --> 10:03.935
I would like to remind
the members of the press

10:04.004 --> 10:06.104
that neither photography
nor sketching will be permitted

10:06.189 --> 10:07.422
while this court's
in session,

10:07.457 --> 10:09.708
though it may resume
during recess.

10:09.776 --> 10:12.143
Counsel, you may continue
jury selection.

10:12.245 --> 10:13.578
Thank you, your honor.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.882
Mr. Lay...
[ babbling ]

10:17.985 --> 10:19.200
...Have you
ever contributed

10:19.252 --> 10:21.786
to either mr. Bryant
or mr. Milam's defense fund?

10:21.888 --> 10:24.055
♪♪

10:24.141 --> 10:27.525
lay: Well, I might have...
Might not have.

10:27.628 --> 10:29.027
[ laughter ]

10:29.062 --> 10:33.164
chatham: Would you please tell
the court how you feel about...

10:36.002 --> 10:38.320
Alright, you be good now.
John: How you
holding up so far?

10:38.355 --> 10:39.854
Mind your granny.
You ready for some lunch?

10:39.906 --> 10:42.123
Mamie:
I don't know that I have much
of an appetite after all that.

10:42.175 --> 10:44.009
But I would like to find
the ladies' room.

10:44.127 --> 10:45.577
The closest
we could use

10:45.646 --> 10:47.062
is over at
james griffin's place --

10:47.147 --> 10:48.246
the diner across town.

10:48.332 --> 10:50.248
We'll take you.
Across town?

10:50.334 --> 10:52.050
Meanwhile, there's
a "whites only" bathroom

10:52.152 --> 10:53.468
on every floor
of the courthouse.

10:53.553 --> 10:55.003
Even the defendants
get to use the one

10:55.088 --> 10:56.338
in the judge's chambers.

10:56.423 --> 10:57.972
We'll have plenty
of time to grab lunch

10:58.058 --> 11:01.176
then make it back to hear
testimony with time to spare.

11:01.261 --> 11:03.228
I say it's a miracle
they found 12 men

11:03.347 --> 11:05.046
who hadn't contributed
to the defense fund --

11:05.148 --> 11:06.881
or at least admitted
to contributing.

11:06.983 --> 11:09.017
They were a motley looking
bunch, weren't they?

11:09.102 --> 11:11.353
[ chuckles ]
well, let's just hope
mr. Chatham selected

11:11.438 --> 11:13.721
a few jurors
with enough good sense

11:13.824 --> 11:15.774
to distinguish truth
from lies.

11:15.859 --> 11:18.276
Yeah.
Sidney: Why, it was just
a few years ago,

11:18.362 --> 11:20.445
j.W. Milam saved
a little negro girl

11:20.547 --> 11:23.231
from drowning
in the tallahatchie river.

11:23.333 --> 11:26.167
He has loaned his own car
to his workers on --

11:26.253 --> 11:29.087
on several occasions,
and once even rushed one

11:29.206 --> 11:31.339
to the hospital when
he'd slashed a vein.

11:31.425 --> 11:33.591
Now, these are not
the actions of a man

11:33.677 --> 11:36.210
with racial hatred
in his heart.

11:36.313 --> 11:39.597
Mr. Milam is loved by all
the negroes in his community.

11:39.683 --> 11:40.932
[ sighs ]

11:41.017 --> 11:48.256
♪♪

11:48.308 --> 11:51.409
that sheriff
has his deputies

11:51.495 --> 11:54.328
frisk the family
of the victim this morning,

11:54.381 --> 11:57.031
then has the gall
to eat lunch with them?

11:57.067 --> 11:59.317
As if they're just
a couple of old pals?

11:59.386 --> 12:00.719
Try not to
focus on them.

12:00.787 --> 12:02.687
But how can I
ignore it?

12:02.756 --> 12:04.339
There is nothing
for me to do here

12:04.374 --> 12:09.327
except sit still
and watch and wait.

12:10.347 --> 12:12.781
Oh, god. Maybe if y'all
could just catch me up

12:12.816 --> 12:16.067
on what you've been working on,
I-I could be of help somehow.

12:16.186 --> 12:19.087
There must be
something I can do.

12:19.172 --> 12:20.472
You showed up.

12:21.808 --> 12:24.142
I know
that wasn't easy.

12:24.227 --> 12:25.527
And it won't be
any easier tomorrow

12:25.562 --> 12:27.796
or the next day,
but it matters.

12:27.881 --> 12:30.432
It really does.

12:30.517 --> 12:32.167
So just keep
showing up.

12:32.252 --> 12:41.409
♪♪

12:41.445 --> 12:44.763
mr. Chatham, mr. Smith.
Y'all have a moment?

12:44.798 --> 12:46.931
I'm sorry, son, but we won't be
making any statements

12:47.000 --> 12:47.899
to the press
at this time.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.400
I'm not looking
for anything.

12:49.469 --> 12:51.202
I have something
for you.

12:51.271 --> 12:53.171
From dr. Howard.

12:53.273 --> 12:55.840
Well, I can't imagine
what he'd have for me.

12:55.926 --> 12:57.242
Witnesses.

12:57.327 --> 12:59.144
He's found at least three
who saw emmett till

12:59.212 --> 13:00.462
on the morning
of his death,

13:00.514 --> 13:02.197
can identify the location
where he was taken --

13:02.232 --> 13:04.299
where his murder
likely occurred.

13:04.334 --> 13:06.284
And they can even place
the defendants there

13:06.353 --> 13:07.902
and confirm they
did not act alone.

13:07.988 --> 13:09.270
Where are these people?

13:09.322 --> 13:11.556
Dr. Howard and his team
will disclose their identities

13:11.608 --> 13:13.358
as soon as they receive
assurances from law enforcement

13:13.426 --> 13:16.227
that they'll be brought
in safely to testify.

13:16.313 --> 13:18.997
But they're gonna need you to
reach out to trusted officials.

13:19.082 --> 13:20.932
No strider.
Understood.

13:21.034 --> 13:22.767
There's more to it
than that.

13:22.853 --> 13:24.502
According to
these witnesses,

13:24.571 --> 13:26.137
till was likely killed
on a plantation

13:26.256 --> 13:28.323
in sunflower county.

13:28.358 --> 13:29.924
Well, if that's true, we'll have
to forfeit this case

13:29.960 --> 13:31.009
over to their
district attorney.

13:31.094 --> 13:32.760
Sanders is chomping
at the bit.

13:32.813 --> 13:35.547
[ chuckles ] I thought
you might be relieved

13:35.615 --> 13:36.915
to have it
off your plate.

13:37.017 --> 13:39.600
It's a tough case.

13:39.686 --> 13:42.053
The kind that legacies
are made from.

13:42.122 --> 13:43.321
Well, it wouldn't be
much of a legacy

13:43.440 --> 13:46.674
if you lost, would it?

13:46.726 --> 13:49.610
Without these witnesses,
that's a strong possibility.

13:49.713 --> 13:55.567
♪♪

13:55.669 --> 13:56.835
bailiff: All rise.

13:56.920 --> 14:01.873
♪♪

14:01.958 --> 14:03.308
court is now in session.

14:03.376 --> 14:04.943
The honorable
judge swango presiding.

14:05.061 --> 14:06.578
You may be seated.

14:10.984 --> 14:12.283
Swango: Court will
now hear the case

14:12.352 --> 14:15.086
of the state of mississippi vs.
Roy bryant and j.W. Milam.

14:15.155 --> 14:16.688
Both sides present,
ready for testimony?

14:16.756 --> 14:18.056
Ready for the defense,
your honor.

14:18.124 --> 14:21.442
Your honor, I'd like
to request a continuance.

14:21.545 --> 14:25.163
[ spectators murmuring ]

14:25.282 --> 14:26.965
[ gavel bangs ]

14:27.050 --> 14:28.850
we're about to begin
testimony, mr. Chatham.

14:28.902 --> 14:30.635
What cause do you have
for delay?

14:30.704 --> 14:33.504
Your honor, moments ago,
our office was informed

14:33.573 --> 14:35.273
of the existence
of several witnesses

14:35.342 --> 14:36.741
previously unknown
to us --

14:36.826 --> 14:38.309
witnesses who could
provide evidence

14:38.395 --> 14:39.878
that could change
the course --

14:39.980 --> 14:42.229
if not the very nature --
of these proceedings.

14:42.332 --> 14:44.682
[ spectators groan ]
I need order in this court.

14:46.436 --> 14:48.720
Please remain quiet while
we discuss this matter further.

14:48.788 --> 14:50.305
Uh, t-the defense has not
been made aware

14:50.390 --> 14:51.940
of any new witnesses,

14:51.992 --> 14:54.208
and we move to exclude
any additional testimony

14:54.294 --> 14:55.894
and that we continue
with the proceedings

14:55.962 --> 14:57.745
without undue delay.

15:00.567 --> 15:02.867
Court finds the state's
position reasonable.

15:02.936 --> 15:04.385
Continuance is granted.

15:04.437 --> 15:07.005
Witness testimony
will begin tomorrow morning.

15:07.090 --> 15:09.440
Court is adjourned for
the remainder of the day.

15:09.526 --> 15:13.044
[ indistinct conversations ]

15:13.146 --> 15:14.295
you knew?

15:15.432 --> 15:17.832
We wanted to tell you, but we
weren't sure how it'd pan out.

15:17.884 --> 15:19.117
We didn't want to get
your hopes up

15:19.185 --> 15:20.385
till medgar here
gave us the all-clear.

15:20.487 --> 15:22.003
Well, tell me now.

15:22.038 --> 15:24.005
Well, we found some
local plantation workers

15:24.057 --> 15:25.690
who either saw
or heard emmett

15:25.792 --> 15:27.725
on the morning
of his disappearance.

15:27.794 --> 15:29.193
They heard him?

15:31.581 --> 15:32.897
Tell me.

15:32.966 --> 15:34.632
What did they hear?

15:35.936 --> 15:38.036
Your son crying out.

15:40.490 --> 15:41.973
Ruby:
They wanted to help.

15:42.042 --> 15:44.275
They just didn't see
how they could.

15:45.946 --> 15:47.879
And it won't be easy to hear
what they have to say,

15:47.948 --> 15:51.132
but if we can get this case
moved to sunflower county,

15:51.167 --> 15:54.719
we are one step closer
to justice for your son.

15:54.788 --> 15:57.055
I hope you're right.

15:57.140 --> 15:58.556
Now, if you'll excuse me,

15:58.658 --> 16:00.942
I think I've had enough
for today.

16:01.027 --> 16:04.345
Um, I'd like to settle in
at dr. Howard's.

16:12.656 --> 16:15.673
[ laughter ]

16:15.759 --> 16:17.608
okay, okay.
Alright.

16:20.380 --> 16:22.814
♪♪

16:22.932 --> 16:24.799
♪ dreaming ♪
♪ dreaming ♪

16:24.901 --> 16:26.651
♪ dreaming ♪
♪ dreaming ♪

16:26.770 --> 16:27.968
♪ here I am dreaming again ♪

16:28.071 --> 16:30.638
♪ here I am dreaming again ♪

16:30.740 --> 16:32.240
♪ dreaming ♪
♪ dreaming ♪

16:32.325 --> 16:34.659
♪ dreaming ♪
♪ just dreaming ♪

16:34.761 --> 16:35.860
♪ I'm in a deep dream again ♪

16:35.962 --> 16:38.646
♪ I'm in a deep dream again ♪

16:38.748 --> 16:40.365
♪ sleeping ♪
♪ sleeping ♪

16:40.450 --> 16:42.250
♪ just a-sleeping ♪

16:42.335 --> 16:47.171
♪ it's time for me to wake up ♪

16:47.273 --> 16:51.092
♪ for no matter how I dream ♪

16:51.177 --> 16:53.628
♪ it always makes me cry ♪

16:53.713 --> 16:56.964
welcome to mound bayou.

16:58.101 --> 16:59.550
[ engine turns off ]

17:03.139 --> 17:04.355
thank you.

17:04.474 --> 17:05.973
[ chuckles ]

17:07.811 --> 17:11.112
it is a pleasure to finally
meet you, mrs. Bradley.

17:11.197 --> 17:13.448
Thank you for opening
your home to us.

17:13.533 --> 17:15.483
I am very grateful.

17:15.568 --> 17:17.017
Ah, mr. Mooty.

17:17.120 --> 17:18.319
It's a real
honor, sir.

17:18.405 --> 17:20.038
Ah, mr. Carthan.

17:20.156 --> 17:21.572
[ chuckles ]
show these gentlemen

17:21.658 --> 17:22.690
to their rooms,
will you?

17:22.792 --> 17:24.575
I'm going to give
mrs. Bradley here

17:24.661 --> 17:27.211
the vip tour.

17:27.330 --> 17:28.329
[ laughs ]

17:28.415 --> 17:30.865
wow.

17:30.967 --> 17:33.384
Did I see a pool
on my way out here?

17:33.503 --> 17:35.002
Oh, indeed, you did.

17:35.088 --> 17:36.871
Where else are our children
going to swim?

17:36.973 --> 17:39.490
[ laughs ]
everything
in our community

17:39.559 --> 17:42.026
is meant to enrich
its people.

17:42.095 --> 17:44.862
Even our hospital
employs an all-negro staff,

17:44.948 --> 17:46.531
so when one of us
is sick,

17:46.649 --> 17:48.082
we can enter through
the front door,

17:48.168 --> 17:49.634
and we can do so knowing

17:49.736 --> 17:51.719
that we'll be heard
and counseled by someone

17:51.821 --> 17:55.456
that can see our pain
and acknowledge it.

17:55.508 --> 17:57.341
And you are
the chief of surgery.

17:57.444 --> 17:59.627
Yes.
My goodness.

17:59.679 --> 18:01.729
I didn't even think a thing
like that was possible.

18:01.815 --> 18:02.930
It wasn't.

18:03.032 --> 18:05.049
Until it was, huh?

18:05.135 --> 18:08.186
Until you made it so?
[ chuckling ]
oh, no, no, no.

18:08.271 --> 18:10.488
Oh, I can't take
the credit, no.

18:10.590 --> 18:14.358
Mound bayou was founded
out of necessity

18:14.444 --> 18:16.427
by isaiah montgomery
and benjamin green.

18:16.496 --> 18:18.379
Now, both men
had been enslaved,

18:18.465 --> 18:21.348
and as soon as they were
free and capable,

18:21.451 --> 18:23.835
they recruited
the best of their people

18:23.920 --> 18:26.687
and turned this town into
a self-reliant community.

18:26.773 --> 18:29.624
A safe haven.
Absolutely.

18:29.676 --> 18:32.426
Well, the settlers had
spent their entire lives

18:32.479 --> 18:34.045
building up this land
for white folks.

18:34.130 --> 18:35.713
They decided it was time
they built something

18:35.832 --> 18:37.115
for themselves, huh?

18:37.183 --> 18:38.733
[ laughs ]

18:38.818 --> 18:41.869
68 years later,
I am humbled

18:41.955 --> 18:44.772
to play a small role
in its continued growth.

18:44.858 --> 18:48.159
It's wonderful --
all of it.

18:48.261 --> 18:50.428
Since I crossed
the state line,

18:50.513 --> 18:53.281
I've been made to feel
like a fugitive.

18:53.333 --> 18:57.251
I feel like I've been
holding my breath for days.

18:57.353 --> 18:59.036
I know the feeling well.

19:01.875 --> 19:05.243
Thank you for giving me
a space where I can breathe.

19:05.328 --> 19:06.244
Of course.

19:06.329 --> 19:07.645
And if there's anything
else I can do

19:07.730 --> 19:11.249
to make you feel more at home,
you just let me know, huh?

19:12.385 --> 19:14.101
There you are.

19:16.022 --> 19:18.506
I'll have our cook
whip up something fine

19:18.541 --> 19:21.409
and southern for supper
at around 6:30.

19:21.494 --> 19:22.860
[ chuckles ]

19:22.946 --> 19:24.462
dr. Howard.

19:24.547 --> 19:27.047
♪♪

19:27.100 --> 19:29.901
you're the freest black man
I've ever met.

19:29.969 --> 19:32.136
You could live anywhere.

19:32.205 --> 19:34.922
Why don't you move
up north?

19:34.958 --> 19:37.424
That pool...

19:37.477 --> 19:39.327
Those children,
this community --

19:39.412 --> 19:42.146
these are my people,

19:42.215 --> 19:44.498
and there is far too much work
to do down here.

19:44.534 --> 19:46.684
If I leave
mississippi...

19:47.854 --> 19:50.004
...I leave them behind.

19:52.859 --> 19:59.530
♪♪

19:59.649 --> 20:06.304
♪♪

20:06.389 --> 20:13.094
♪♪

20:13.179 --> 20:14.412
willie reed?

20:15.865 --> 20:17.548
You're a hard one
to find.

20:17.617 --> 20:19.684
My name is mr. Sanders,
and I'm a district attorney

20:19.769 --> 20:21.919
in sunflower county.

20:22.005 --> 20:25.022
And I heard you know something
about that chicago boy.

20:25.108 --> 20:26.624
The boy from the papers?

20:26.693 --> 20:29.026
No, I don--
I don't know nothing, sir.

20:29.112 --> 20:30.728
Willie, these men here
just spent half a day

20:30.813 --> 20:33.130
trying to track you down.

20:33.216 --> 20:35.900
Now, I know you're not
gonna waste our time.

20:36.002 --> 20:38.719
Well, I-I think I seen him

20:38.755 --> 20:40.605
on the back of some truck.

20:41.741 --> 20:43.457
Whereabouts?

20:43.509 --> 20:46.727
Down by the sturdivant property.
Sir.

20:46.813 --> 20:48.746
That confirms it.

20:48.815 --> 20:49.947
If all goes
as it should,

20:50.016 --> 20:51.716
we'll be taking over
from tallahatchie county

20:51.784 --> 20:54.185
and you'll be called in
as a witness for the state.

20:54.304 --> 20:56.087
♪♪

20:56.155 --> 20:58.589
now, you understand
what that means?

20:58.675 --> 20:59.624
Yes, sir.

20:59.726 --> 21:01.192
Now, normally,
we'd be taking you in

21:01.277 --> 21:02.693
to give your
official statement,

21:02.762 --> 21:04.128
but we know tensions
are a little hot

21:04.213 --> 21:06.464
right now
amongst the negroes.

21:06.532 --> 21:08.599
So we've worked out a deal
with that doctor fella

21:08.701 --> 21:11.118
down in mound bayou.

21:11.154 --> 21:12.670
You heard of him?

21:12.755 --> 21:14.555
Dr. Howard.
Yes, sir.

21:14.641 --> 21:16.190
Well, he's offered up
his home if you feel

21:16.276 --> 21:17.875
the need for protection
during the trial.

21:17.944 --> 21:20.811
Well, what about
after the trial, sir?

21:20.897 --> 21:23.581
What are we supposed
to do then?

21:23.666 --> 21:26.284
Leave the questions
to me.

21:26.319 --> 21:28.252
Now, we're asking you to meet
out there at his place

21:28.354 --> 21:31.689
at 6:00 tonight
to give your statement,

21:31.808 --> 21:33.557
and we're asking you
to come willingly.

21:35.144 --> 21:36.978
But we're not
gonna ask twice.

21:37.063 --> 21:44.151
♪♪

21:44.237 --> 21:57.698
♪♪
mighty fine place
you have here, dr. Howard.

21:57.750 --> 22:00.318
I admit --
never seen a negro

22:00.386 --> 22:03.004
in such a home before.

22:03.039 --> 22:05.189
Not legally, anyway.
[ chuckles ]

22:06.259 --> 22:08.125
I think the folks
at the tax board

22:08.194 --> 22:09.493
must share
your astonishment,

22:09.562 --> 22:11.862
considering how many times
I've been audited.

22:11.931 --> 22:16.567
But rest assured, gentlemen --
it all checks out.

22:16.669 --> 22:18.636
♪♪

22:18.738 --> 22:21.372
it's been
nearly an hour.

22:21.457 --> 22:22.556
[ sighs ] I don't think
they're coming.

22:22.642 --> 22:23.808
If we had taken them
into custody,

22:23.876 --> 22:25.476
this would've been
a whole lot simpler.

22:25.545 --> 22:27.078
If you had taken them
into custody,

22:27.146 --> 22:29.747
they never would've felt
safe enough to tell the truth

22:29.816 --> 22:31.482
the way they did with us.

22:31.551 --> 22:33.984
Do I need to remind you
folks our boys tracked down

22:34.070 --> 22:35.436
the witnesses
y'all failed to locate?

22:35.521 --> 22:36.937
You tracked them down
by threatening

22:37.040 --> 22:38.489
and intimidating
the community

22:38.591 --> 22:39.924
that was trying
to keep them safe,

22:39.992 --> 22:41.525
and the only reason
they are not here now

22:41.627 --> 22:43.377
is because<i> you</i>
and your posse

22:43.429 --> 22:45.563
scared the living daylights
out of everyone.

22:45.648 --> 22:47.465
All the locals are saying
they thought you were fbi.

22:47.550 --> 22:48.833
She goes on talking
this way to me,

22:48.918 --> 22:50.735
we're gonna have
a problem.

22:50.853 --> 22:52.453
♪♪

22:52.538 --> 22:53.838
dr. Howard: Enough!

22:53.923 --> 22:56.741
♪♪

22:56.809 --> 22:59.593
we all want the same thing
here, don't we?

22:59.679 --> 23:02.546
♪♪

23:02.615 --> 23:04.682
we want these
witnesses to talk.

23:04.784 --> 23:07.918
We want the best possible chance
at a fair trial down here.

23:08.004 --> 23:09.253
And you, sheriff smith?

23:09.372 --> 23:11.021
The same thing.

23:11.107 --> 23:13.891
And we want the trial moved
out of strider's jurisdiction.

23:13.960 --> 23:17.645
Then I'd say the answer
to my question is yes, correct?

23:17.697 --> 23:19.196
If the law says
the case is mine,

23:19.298 --> 23:21.549
then I want to win --
simple as that.

23:21.601 --> 23:23.434
Well, in order to win,
you need these witnesses

23:23.536 --> 23:24.502
to come forward.

23:24.604 --> 23:26.036
He's right, stanny.

23:26.105 --> 23:27.805
These witnesses have
a story to tell,

23:27.840 --> 23:31.609
and we just need to make them
feel safe enough to tell it.

23:31.677 --> 23:35.262
And I think working together
is the best chance we've got.

23:35.348 --> 23:38.015
Even if it takes
all night.

23:38.117 --> 23:44.088
♪♪

23:44.190 --> 23:50.177
♪♪

23:50.229 --> 23:51.962
mandy, d--

23:52.031 --> 23:53.831
please, ma'am.

23:53.900 --> 23:56.700
I was wrong about
what I said before, ma'am.

23:57.804 --> 23:59.253
I got confused.

23:59.305 --> 24:01.222
B-but I didn't
see nothing, I swear.

24:01.307 --> 24:02.440
[ stammers ]

24:02.525 --> 24:05.209
just give us
a minute, please.

24:05.294 --> 24:06.911
♪♪

24:06.979 --> 24:11.132
look, I said something to you
before that's been nagging me.

24:11.167 --> 24:12.966
I said that
if you spoke up,

24:13.019 --> 24:15.653
you'd be risking
your livelihood.

24:15.721 --> 24:18.289
Well, that was a-a stupid
thing for me to say,

24:18.391 --> 24:21.459
and I apologize, because
we both know damn well

24:21.544 --> 24:24.311
that you'd be risking a whole
hell of a lot more than that.

24:24.363 --> 24:27.848
You'd be risking
your life to testify.

24:27.900 --> 24:29.816
I just want to keep
my family safe.

24:29.919 --> 24:31.135
I know, I know.

24:31.220 --> 24:33.904
And I promise you,
they will be.

24:33.990 --> 24:36.623
We have all the resources
of the naacp

24:36.676 --> 24:39.109
and dr. Howard
to protect you --

24:39.178 --> 24:41.145
and not just during
the trial,

24:41.214 --> 24:42.580
but afterwards, too.

24:47.904 --> 24:50.254
I-I can't just
leave my granddaddy.

24:50.339 --> 24:52.122
Well, he could
go with you.

24:52.158 --> 24:54.792
A-and dr. Howard will provide
financial assistance

24:54.861 --> 24:56.376
until you can both
get on your feet up there.

24:56.429 --> 24:58.529
We don't need
no handout.

24:58.598 --> 25:00.548
Never have.
I work hard.

25:00.600 --> 25:02.283
So does my grandson.

25:02.368 --> 25:04.935
He's just starting
to make his own way.

25:05.004 --> 25:07.855
So why would he want
to throw all that away

25:07.940 --> 25:09.957
by talking in court
about somethin'

25:10.009 --> 25:12.309
that ain't none
of his business anyhow?

25:12.411 --> 25:14.912
Because if he speaks up
about what he saw,

25:15.014 --> 25:17.448
he can help change the way
things go around here for us.

25:17.550 --> 25:20.867
And you'll both be free
to start again in chicago.

25:20.970 --> 25:22.035
Free to make
a better life

25:22.138 --> 25:24.455
where you aren't
living like slaves.

25:27.043 --> 25:29.493
Ain't nothin' wrong with
the life we got here now.

25:29.595 --> 25:31.128
A life where you can't
speak the truth

25:31.197 --> 25:33.597
for fear of what will
happen to you after?

25:33.666 --> 25:36.000
What kind of life
is that?

25:36.085 --> 25:39.537
Now, I am telling you,
there is a better way,

25:39.622 --> 25:42.172
but it has to start
with all of us.

25:51.968 --> 25:53.284
Come in.

25:53.386 --> 25:55.319
Oh.
[ both chuckle ]

25:55.388 --> 25:57.454
I hear you missed dinner.
Is everything okay?

25:57.557 --> 25:59.924
Oh, I apologize.

26:00.026 --> 26:02.092
Time slipped away,
I suppose.

26:02.161 --> 26:03.176
It's my fault.

26:03.229 --> 26:05.396
I-I should've sent someone
to check on you.

26:05.464 --> 26:07.881
It's been hard to get away
with all of the excitement

26:07.934 --> 26:09.466
trying to track down
those witnesses.

26:09.535 --> 26:10.951
Any progress?

26:11.003 --> 26:13.470
We shall see
in the morning.

26:13.539 --> 26:15.439
I hope I haven't
come off as rude.

26:15.541 --> 26:17.391
It's just, every time
I try to leave,

26:17.476 --> 26:20.511
the sky keeps
pulling me back in.

26:20.613 --> 26:23.447
It's not like this
in chicago.
Hmm.

26:23.549 --> 26:25.382
So many stars.

26:25.484 --> 26:27.518
Yeah.

26:27.587 --> 26:30.387
It makes me wonder if emmett
had a chance to see them.

26:30.473 --> 26:32.356
♪♪

26:32.425 --> 26:34.358
I want to believe he did.

26:34.460 --> 26:36.060
♪♪

26:36.128 --> 26:38.896
sounds like you're having
a hard time, though --

26:38.965 --> 26:40.598
believing.

26:40.700 --> 26:42.032
I am.

26:43.736 --> 26:47.771
And I'm ashamed to say
that when I got here,

26:47.840 --> 26:50.007
I was angry
at my uncle mose.

26:50.076 --> 26:51.342
I-I --
I couldn't say it,

26:51.410 --> 26:55.045
but I-I felt it
in the pit of my stomach,

26:55.114 --> 26:57.031
for him promising
to give emmett

26:57.083 --> 27:00.384
the summer camp
experience.

27:00.469 --> 27:01.785
And now?

27:03.306 --> 27:04.655
The anger's gone.

27:04.757 --> 27:06.523
♪♪

27:06.592 --> 27:08.575
I just -- I feel
so sorry for him,

27:08.661 --> 27:11.095
because he believed.

27:11.163 --> 27:15.833
He really thought he could
give that to my boy.

27:15.901 --> 27:19.503
Do you think it's possible
for a black boy in mississippi

27:19.605 --> 27:21.138
to see the stars?

27:21.207 --> 27:24.708
Well, if I didn't, I wouldn't be
fighting like I do.

27:24.777 --> 27:27.411
Fighting so that
the next generation

27:27.480 --> 27:30.214
can live
without fear and...

27:30.282 --> 27:32.216
Be fully human.

27:32.284 --> 27:34.518
♪♪

27:34.587 --> 27:35.886
and see the stars.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.088
But what about now?

27:38.157 --> 27:39.440
Are men like uncle mose

27:39.492 --> 27:41.859
supposed to keep
living by the code?

27:41.961 --> 27:44.461
Suppressing their emotions
to get by?

27:44.547 --> 27:45.796
I mean, that's
no kind of life.

27:45.865 --> 27:47.197
Well, that's the life
he's always known.

27:47.266 --> 27:49.116
I don't know.

27:49.201 --> 27:52.136
♪♪

27:52.204 --> 27:54.638
maybe white folks
down here...

27:54.707 --> 27:57.207
Don't think
we have feelings.

27:57.309 --> 27:59.810
♪♪

27:59.879 --> 28:03.447
if they did, how could they
treat us like they do?

28:03.566 --> 28:05.382
Mamie.

28:05.484 --> 28:07.584
You are showing them
that we do feel --

28:07.653 --> 28:11.155
that we hurt like them,
that we love like them.

28:11.223 --> 28:16.026
You opened that casket
so they'd see your pain.

28:16.095 --> 28:19.063
You showed up so they
could see your love.

28:19.165 --> 28:21.765
And what if
they're blind to it?

28:21.834 --> 28:24.368
You have more faith
than that.

28:24.453 --> 28:26.470
I used to think so.

28:27.907 --> 28:29.406
But the "code" will
serve uncle mose

28:29.492 --> 28:31.375
on the stand tomorrow.

28:31.444 --> 28:33.911
He will fall in line.

28:33.996 --> 28:35.879
I don't suppose every
black man down here

28:35.981 --> 28:38.515
could be as brave
as you are, dr. Howard.

28:38.601 --> 28:40.751
♪♪

28:40.836 --> 28:42.753
my means
have afforded me

28:42.872 --> 28:46.390
the privilege
of raising hell.

28:47.460 --> 28:50.594
But I assure you,
mrs. Bradley,

28:50.663 --> 28:53.113
any witness who takes
that stand tomorrow

28:53.165 --> 28:55.349
is doing so knowing
that they are putting

28:55.384 --> 28:57.101
everything on the line.

28:57.203 --> 29:00.070
♪♪

29:00.139 --> 29:03.941
courage looks different
on every man.

29:04.026 --> 29:06.627
[ indistinct conversations ]

29:06.712 --> 29:12.966
♪♪

29:13.052 --> 29:19.306
♪♪

29:19.391 --> 29:21.258
oh, excuse me,
young man.

29:21.360 --> 29:22.826
S-sorry, ma'am.

29:22.912 --> 29:24.178
That's quite alright.

29:24.213 --> 29:30.884
♪♪

29:30.920 --> 29:33.437
I didn't see her.
I'm sorry.

29:33.556 --> 29:35.873
It's okay, simmy.

29:35.975 --> 29:38.709
♪♪

29:38.811 --> 29:40.861
it's okay, son.

29:40.913 --> 29:43.464
If they call me,
what are they gon' ask?

29:43.499 --> 29:46.183
What you saw that night
they took bobo -- that's all.

29:46.268 --> 29:48.952
After I tell them,
can I come home?

29:51.690 --> 29:53.807
When are things
gonna go back?

30:02.668 --> 30:05.135
They're not
going back, son.

30:06.572 --> 30:07.988
[ indistinct conversations ]

30:08.090 --> 30:14.628
♪♪

30:14.730 --> 30:21.301
♪♪

30:21.387 --> 30:27.991
♪♪

30:28.077 --> 30:30.978
[ sighs ] they've been
in there for ages.

30:31.013 --> 30:33.013
Chatham has to clear
each witness with the judge

30:33.065 --> 30:35.766
and the defense before
they can be admitted.

30:35.851 --> 30:37.201
Hopefully, they're just
being thorough.

30:37.303 --> 30:38.869
[ door opens ]

30:38.938 --> 30:46.026
♪♪

30:46.128 --> 30:53.199
♪♪

30:53.285 --> 31:00.357
♪♪

31:00.442 --> 31:02.092
[ door closes ]

31:03.879 --> 31:06.363
the court has made
a decision.

31:06.448 --> 31:07.497
The state
will be permitted

31:07.566 --> 31:08.832
to call on these
new witnesses

31:08.901 --> 31:10.834
to present their testimony
to the jury tomorrow.

31:10.920 --> 31:12.185
[ indistinct conversations ]

31:12.271 --> 31:14.705
but the trial will
remain in sumner.

31:14.807 --> 31:16.423
[ indistinct conversations ]

31:23.432 --> 31:25.282
I guess we're stuck
with sheriff strider.

31:25.384 --> 31:27.918
Why isn't
the trial moving?

31:27.987 --> 31:30.537
I can only assume that the judge
didn't believe

31:30.623 --> 31:32.856
there was enough
evidence to prove

31:32.925 --> 31:35.141
that the murder occurred
on that plantation.

31:35.244 --> 31:36.693
But he's allowing them
to testify.

31:36.779 --> 31:39.579
Doesn't that mean
he finds them credible?

31:39.632 --> 31:41.381
He, uh, might
find it credible

31:41.433 --> 31:43.584
that emmett
was brought there,

31:43.619 --> 31:44.668
but what actually
happened there

31:44.770 --> 31:47.271
might require
more convincing.

31:47.373 --> 31:49.072
Either way, the fact
that the jury will get

31:49.141 --> 31:52.009
to hear from them at all
is still a big victory for us.

31:53.445 --> 31:55.679
[ gavel bangs ]
swango: This court
is now in session.

31:55.781 --> 31:57.547
The state may call
its first witness.

31:59.401 --> 32:01.618
Thank you, your honor.

32:01.704 --> 32:05.338
The state would like to call
to the stand mose wright.

32:05.424 --> 32:07.057
[ indistinct conversations ]

32:09.395 --> 32:11.111
[ door opens ]

32:11.196 --> 32:18.535
♪♪

32:18.621 --> 32:25.976
♪♪

32:26.078 --> 32:33.417
♪♪

32:33.519 --> 32:45.746
♪♪
it was August 28th...

32:45.831 --> 32:48.415
At about 2:00
in the morning.

32:48.500 --> 32:52.202
I woke up and heard someone
at the front door saying,

32:52.287 --> 32:53.870
"preacher, preacher."

32:53.956 --> 32:58.475
and when I got there,
I asked who it was.

32:58.544 --> 33:01.345
He said,
"this is mr. Bryant,

33:01.447 --> 33:04.414
and I want to talk to you
and that boy."

33:04.533 --> 33:05.916
what did you do?

33:06.018 --> 33:07.818
Well, I got up,

33:07.886 --> 33:09.786
opened the door...

33:09.872 --> 33:11.922
And...

33:11.991 --> 33:15.225
Mr. Milam
was standing there

33:15.294 --> 33:17.027
with a pistol
in his right hand

33:17.129 --> 33:21.614
and a flashlight
in his left hand.

33:21.717 --> 33:23.000
Now, I want you
to stop right there

33:23.085 --> 33:25.686
for a minute,
uncle mose.

33:25.738 --> 33:29.006
I want you to point out
mr. Milam

33:29.124 --> 33:31.108
if you can see him
in here.

33:38.484 --> 33:39.966
There he is.

33:42.921 --> 33:45.672
[ spectators murmuring ]

33:48.227 --> 33:51.428
and do you see
mr. Bryant in here?

33:58.987 --> 34:03.056
Chatham: Now...
After you opened the door,

34:03.142 --> 34:04.841
what happened next?

34:04.910 --> 34:07.794
Well, mr. Milam said,

34:07.846 --> 34:10.113
"I want that boy that done all
the talkin' down at money."

34:10.232 --> 34:11.815
and what did you do?

34:11.884 --> 34:13.784
We went to a bedroom,

34:13.852 --> 34:17.921
and we found emmett
and simeon in there.

34:17.990 --> 34:21.324
And, uh, mr. Milam
told him to get up,

34:21.410 --> 34:24.061
so they got up and dressed,
and they started out.

34:24.129 --> 34:25.796
And what happened
after that?

34:25.864 --> 34:28.481
Mr. Milam asked me,
"how old are you?"

34:28.584 --> 34:29.666
I said 64.

34:29.768 --> 34:33.170
He said, "well...If you know

34:33.288 --> 34:35.172
any of us here tonight,

34:35.240 --> 34:39.643
then you will never live
to get to be 65."

34:39.711 --> 34:41.711
[ spectators murmuring ]

34:45.217 --> 34:48.985
and then, did they leave
your house with emmett till?

34:49.071 --> 34:50.120
Yes, sir.

34:50.189 --> 34:51.755
What, if anything,
did you see

34:51.824 --> 34:54.224
when mr. Milam
and mr. Bryant

34:54.309 --> 34:56.226
took emmett out
in front of your house?

34:56.295 --> 34:59.196
I saw a truck headed off
toward money.

34:59.264 --> 35:01.665
Before mr. Milam
and mr. Bryant

35:01.767 --> 35:03.116
got to the truck
with emmett till,

35:03.202 --> 35:04.450
did you hear them
make any statement

35:04.553 --> 35:06.603
or ask anyone
any question?

35:06.688 --> 35:07.604
I sure did.

35:07.673 --> 35:10.340
They asked
if this is the boy,

35:10.409 --> 35:12.109
and someone said yes.

35:12.227 --> 35:14.744
Hmm.

35:14.813 --> 35:18.465
Was that a man's voice
you heard

35:18.550 --> 35:20.600
or a lady's voice
you heard?

35:20.652 --> 35:23.503
Well, I-it seemed lighter
than a man's voice.

35:23.555 --> 35:26.556
Did you say it seemed
like a louder voice?

35:26.658 --> 35:29.426
Lighter.
Lighter voice.

35:31.663 --> 35:36.133
Now, I want you to tell
the court and the jury,

35:36.218 --> 35:37.467
when was the next time --

35:37.586 --> 35:39.719
after emmett till was taken
from your house --

35:39.771 --> 35:42.455
that you saw either him
or his body?

35:45.110 --> 35:48.495
I saw his body when he was
taken out of the river.

35:48.580 --> 35:50.380
I want you
to tell the jury

35:50.449 --> 35:53.917
whether or not you could
tell whose body it was.

35:54.036 --> 35:55.185
Yes, sir.

35:57.122 --> 35:58.488
It was emmett till.

35:58.574 --> 36:00.841
[ spectators murmuring ]

36:00.926 --> 36:02.559
now, when you first
saw the body,

36:02.661 --> 36:03.843
did you notice
whether or not

36:03.946 --> 36:07.447
the undertaker took a ring
off of emmett's finger?

36:07.549 --> 36:09.533
Yes, sir, he sure did.

36:17.192 --> 36:19.292
Is this the ring that
the undertaker took off

36:19.378 --> 36:22.345
of emmett's finger
that morning?

36:22.431 --> 36:23.914
Yes, sir, it is.

36:35.644 --> 36:37.494
No further questions,
your honor.

36:39.581 --> 36:41.865
Mose, when the two men came
to your house that night,

36:41.934 --> 36:44.467
as you say, was anybody else
with them at that time?

36:44.570 --> 36:45.602
Yes, sir.

36:45.704 --> 36:47.971
There was a man who stood
by the screen door.

36:48.040 --> 36:49.806
And how
was he standing?

36:49.875 --> 36:52.976
[ stammers ] he was, uh,
standin' kind of with his --

36:53.045 --> 36:56.179
his head down,
like this here -- peering.

36:56.248 --> 36:57.981
He was trying to hide,
it looked like.

36:58.050 --> 36:59.249
In other words, you think
he was trying to hide

36:59.334 --> 37:00.383
to keep you
from seeing him?

37:00.452 --> 37:01.585
Yes, sir, that's right.

37:01.653 --> 37:03.486
And I believe you said
before that you thought

37:03.572 --> 37:04.537
he was a colored man.

37:04.623 --> 37:05.589
Is that right?
Yes, sir.

37:05.674 --> 37:07.307
He -- he acted
like a colored man.

37:07.392 --> 37:09.659
[ laughter ]

37:14.866 --> 37:18.635
now, you say mr. Milam had
a flashlight in his hand.

37:18.754 --> 37:20.036
Where was that
flashlight pointed?

37:20.105 --> 37:22.188
It was out like this
at me.

37:22.241 --> 37:24.424
And, uh, did you ever have
any lights turned on

37:24.459 --> 37:25.825
in your house while
those men were in there?

37:25.911 --> 37:28.011
No, sir.
Hmm.

37:28.080 --> 37:31.248
And did mr. Milam ever shine
the light in his own face?

37:31.333 --> 37:33.683
No, but I could see
from the light.

37:33.752 --> 37:36.886
You know how it will shine out
from the side like that?

37:40.142 --> 37:41.941
Ah.

37:42.194 --> 37:46.229
Mose, uh, y-you talked to me
over at my office last week,

37:46.315 --> 37:47.397
is that right?
That's right.

37:47.516 --> 37:49.783
Is it a fact, mose,
that on that day

37:49.868 --> 37:52.269
you told me and my colleagues
that you thought

37:52.354 --> 37:54.738
this was mr. Milam
in your house that night

37:54.806 --> 37:58.758
because he was a big man
with a bald head?

37:58.844 --> 37:59.943
That's right, sir.

38:00.028 --> 38:01.745
And the first time
that you ever saw him

38:01.863 --> 38:03.196
was when they came into
this courtroom,

38:03.282 --> 38:04.347
isn't that right?

38:04.433 --> 38:06.650
No, I-I-I knew them
from that night, sir.

38:06.752 --> 38:08.601
But the only reason you say
you know him now

38:08.654 --> 38:11.304
because the man at your house
had a bald head,

38:11.390 --> 38:13.973
isn't that right?

38:14.026 --> 38:18.545
No, I-I-I knowed his face
a-and his stature.

38:20.165 --> 38:23.099
I knowed his face just like
I see him sitting there now.

38:25.270 --> 38:27.187
You changed your story,
haven't you?

38:29.574 --> 38:30.623
They was at my house.

38:30.659 --> 38:31.991
No, the only thing you saw
at your house,

38:32.044 --> 38:36.980
the only man you saw was
bald-headed, isn't that right?

38:37.082 --> 38:39.182
Well...

38:39.301 --> 38:40.684
No.

38:40.769 --> 38:43.436
I-I mean,
yes, that's right.

38:43.538 --> 38:45.322
And isn't it a fact
that you told me

38:45.424 --> 38:46.673
and these
other gentlemen here

38:46.758 --> 38:48.274
that you saw mr. Milam
in the newspaper

38:48.360 --> 38:50.927
before you
saw him in the courtroom?

38:50.996 --> 38:52.162
I don't remember
saying that.

38:52.230 --> 38:54.464
Do you deny
saying that to me?

38:54.533 --> 38:56.483
I don't remember.
[ clears throat ]

38:56.535 --> 38:59.285
mose, did you ever see the light
shining in the face

38:59.338 --> 39:01.971
of the man you say
identified himself

39:02.057 --> 39:04.374
as mr. Bryant that night?

39:04.459 --> 39:05.375
No, sir.

39:05.494 --> 39:08.094
Had you ever seen him
before that?

39:08.180 --> 39:09.245
Not to know him.

39:09.314 --> 39:10.980
Have you ever
been in his store?

39:11.049 --> 39:12.182
I never have.

39:12.284 --> 39:13.866
And the first time you ever
saw mr. Bryant

39:13.969 --> 39:16.419
was in the courtroom
this week, wasn't it?

39:16.505 --> 39:19.589
The first time I ever
saw his face, that's right.

39:19.658 --> 39:23.476
Now, mose, the only
reason you identified
that man as mr. Bryant

39:23.528 --> 39:26.830
is due to the fact
that he said he was mr. Bryant.

39:26.898 --> 39:29.165
Isn't that right?

39:29.267 --> 39:30.400
That's right.

39:30.469 --> 39:34.604
Now, let's, uh --
let's go on up there...

39:37.292 --> 39:41.411
...To the morning
on the river, mose.

39:43.448 --> 39:46.332
Isn't it a fact that you
only identified the body

39:46.385 --> 39:48.101
as that of emmett till's

39:48.186 --> 39:50.220
because it didn't have
any whiskers?

39:50.288 --> 39:52.122
And so you figured it was
the body of a child,

39:52.190 --> 39:54.724
and since
emmett had gone missing,

39:54.843 --> 39:57.227
you just assumed
it was him.

39:57.312 --> 39:59.112
I never mentioned
no missing.

39:59.214 --> 40:02.048
Mose, do you deny that
you made this statement?

40:02.134 --> 40:03.233
No, I did not say it.

40:03.301 --> 40:04.284
You did not
make that statement?

40:04.369 --> 40:06.803
No!
I did not make it!

40:06.922 --> 40:22.202
♪♪

40:31.880 --> 40:33.913
I'm so sorry.

40:34.015 --> 40:36.783
They got me so flustered
up there.

40:36.868 --> 40:39.319
Made a fool of me.
Don't apologize.

40:39.404 --> 40:41.754
Mamie?
For anything.

40:48.079 --> 40:52.348
They're not gonna call
simmy to testify.

40:52.417 --> 40:54.317
Did mr. Chatham say
why he changed his mind?

40:54.402 --> 41:00.256
No, and I-I know
I shouldn't be relieved, but...

41:00.342 --> 41:02.142
If they'd gone at him the way
they went at me,

41:02.227 --> 41:04.327
I'd have
full-out lost it.

41:04.396 --> 41:08.948
They tried to tear you down
and keep you small.

41:09.034 --> 41:12.685
That could've broken any man,
but it didn't break you.

41:12.771 --> 41:14.053
Not today.

41:14.139 --> 41:16.573
Not in the 60-somethin' years
leading up to this day.

41:16.691 --> 41:18.258
[ chuckles ]

41:18.343 --> 41:24.731
when you stood up to them,
you stood up for emmett.

41:24.783 --> 41:28.084
What you did in there
took courage.

41:28.170 --> 41:32.805
Well, I spent my whole life
with my head down,

41:32.908 --> 41:35.024
only looking up
when I was talking to god.

41:35.110 --> 41:38.895
♪♪

41:38.964 --> 41:40.680
but I'm starting
to think

41:40.765 --> 41:44.584
that the sky
is just too beautiful...

41:44.619 --> 41:46.336
Not to keep my head up.

41:46.421 --> 41:53.359
♪♪

41:53.445 --> 42:00.433
♪♪

42:00.519 --> 42:03.036
it ain't easy
looking up.

42:03.121 --> 42:05.004
I know.

42:05.090 --> 42:07.040
I know that now.

42:07.125 --> 42:08.825
I do.

42:08.927 --> 42:10.393
I'm gonna try.

42:10.495 --> 42:15.999
♪♪

42:16.084 --> 42:20.520
you promise me...
That you do the same

42:20.605 --> 42:23.089
when you're up there
on that stand tomorrow.

42:23.191 --> 42:26.042
♪♪

42:26.161 --> 42:28.127
you hear me?

42:28.163 --> 42:29.746
I'll try.

42:29.831 --> 42:45.128
♪♪

42:46.982 --> 42:55.405
♪♪

42:55.507 --> 43:04.013
♪♪

43:04.099 --> 43:12.638
♪♪

43:12.741 --> 43:21.197
♪♪

43:21.299 --> 43:29.806
♪♪

43:29.908 --> 43:38.414
♪♪

43:38.516 --> 43:54.464
♪♪
